  "texts": [
    "In particular, this limited the robustness and precision of the learned preferences, which then impeded user satisfaction in the applied steering.",
    "As such, we asked the participants to concentrate on the interaction modality of the interfaces in their post-task interviews rather than their reflection on the personalization quality.",
    "ConclusionWe demonstrate how activation steering can be applied towards personalizing LLMs in preference-driven tasks.",
    "Through a series of robust computational experiments, we quantify the effects of steering across five LLM models and five preference dimensions.",
    "We then develop three interaction modalities for steerable chatbots and compare their results at personalization and how they are perceived by end users."
  ]
